20restaurant%20on%20the%20famed%20Boulevard%20de%20Clichy%20in%20Paris'%20Pigalle%20neighbourhood%20on%20Saturday%2C%20wearing%20her%20dress%20backwards.%20Authorities%20in%20Paris%20confirmed%20that%20a%20%26quot%3Bgang-rape%26quot%3B%20likely%20took%20place%20between%20Friday%20and%20Saturday%2C%20and%20an%20investigation%20is%20currently%20underway.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELocal%20media%20reported%20that%20the%20woman%20took%20refuge%20in%20a%20kebab%20shop%20in%20the%20Pigalle%20district%20with%20her%20dress%20partially%20torn%20off.%20Restaurant%20owners%20called%20for%20help%20upon%20seeing%20her%20state%2C%20and%20she%20was%20attended%20to%20by%20firefighters%20before%20being%20taken%20to%20Bichat%20Hospital%20for%20a%20medical%20examination.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20timing%20of%20this%20incident%20is%20particularly%20troubling%20as%20security%20officials%20are%20already%20grappling%20with%20a%20multitude%20of%20potential%20threats%2C%20including%20terrorist%20attacks%2C%20cyberattacks%2C%20crowd%20crushes%2C%20and%20the%20impact%20of%20potential%20labour%20strikes%20during%20the%20Olympics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStrath%20Gordon%2C%20Chief%20of%20Public%20Affairs%20and%20Communication%20for%20Australia's%20Olympic%20team%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fworld%2F2024%2F07%2F23%2Fparis-attack-olympics-australia%2F%5C%22%3Estated%20%3C%2Fa%3Ethat%20Australian%20athletes%20in%20Paris%20had%20been%20informed%20of%20the%20alleged%20attack.%20%26quot%3BThey%20are%20advised%20not%20to%20wear%20team%20kit%20when%20in%20public%20places%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Gordon%20said%20in%20an%20email%20on%20Tuesday.%20He%20emphasized%20that%20the%20athletes%20had%20not%20received%20any%20threats%20since%20their%20arrival%20in%20France%20and%20were%20%26quot%3Bgetting%20on%20with%20their%20preparations%20for%20the%20Games.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Australian%20consulate%20and%20French%20police%20are%20providing%20support%20to%20the%20victim.%20Anna%20Meares%2C%20the%20Australian%20chef%20de%20mission%2C%20expressed%20her%20shock%20and%20concern%20over%20the%20incident.%20%26quot%3BI%20have%20been%20informed%2C%20it%20sounds%20horrific.%20Obviously%2C%20our%20hearts%20go%20out%20to%20the%20woman%20involved%2C%20and%20we%20hope%20she's%20being%20cared%20for%20and%20supported%20in%20the%20trauma%20she's%20experienced%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Faustralia-news%2Farticle%2F2024%2Fjul%2F23%2Folympic-officials-briefed-after-australian-woman-allegedly-raped-by-five-men-in-paris%5C%22%3EMs%20Meares%20said%20on%20Tuesday%20morning.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMs%20Meares%20reiterated%20that%20team%20members%20had%20been%20thoroughly%20briefed%20on%20security%20and%20safety%20precautions.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20information%20we're%20passing%20on%20to%20our%20athletes%20is%20that%20security%20presence%20is%20really%2C%20really%20high%20and%20that's%20in%20order%20for%20them%20to%20act%20as%20quickly%20as%20possible%20to%20keep%20them%20safe%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fsport%2Farticle%2F2024%2Fjul%2F24%2Fsignificant-assault-two-staff-from-nines-olympic-broadcast-team-attacked-in-paris-in-suspected-robbery%5C%22%3Eshe%20said%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20yet%20have%20any%20feedback%20from%20our%20athletes%20that%20they%20have%20felt%20unsafe.%20We%20are%20encouraging%20them%2C%20if%20they%20go%20out%20of%20the%20village%2C%20not%20to%20go%20out%20on%20their%20own%2C%20not%20to%20wear%20team%20uniform%2C%20just%20to%20wear%20plain%20clothes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Australian%20Department%20of%20Foreign%20Affairs%20and%20Trade%20is%20working%20to%20confirm%20the%20details%20of%20the%20incident.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Australian%20embassy%20in%20Paris%20is%20making%20urgent%20inquiries%20with%20French%20authorities%20following%20reports%20of%20an%20Australian%20citizen%20assaulted%20in%20Paris%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20spokespers