-things-to-do-portable-waterproof-solar-cooker-how-to-make-lifestyle%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esolar%20cooking%20%3C%2Fa%3Ewas%20the%20alternative%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReva%20decided%20to%20discard%20LPG%20cylinders%20completely%20in%202020.%20Prior%20to%20that%2C%20she%20was%20using%20LPG%20cylinders%20that%20required%20to%20be%20refilled%20once%20every%202-3%20months.%20Along%20with%20LPG%2C%20she%20was%20using%20her%20parents%E2%80%99%20solar%20cooker%20intermittently.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20realised%20we%20can%20actually%20go%20without%20LPG.%20In%20our%20country%2C%20the%20sun%20is%20so%20abundantly%20available%20to%20us%2C%20why%20not%20harness%20this%20energy%20as%20much%20as%20we%20can%3F%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20solar%20cooking%20has%20become%20a%20primary%20source%20of%20cooking%20for%20Reva.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-cooking-3-1721205686.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Reva%20finds%20immense%20satisfaction%20knowing%20her%20food%20is%20cooked%20in%20sunlight%20effortlessly.%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-cooking-3-1721205686.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-cooking-3-1721205686-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-cooking-3-1721205686-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-cooking-3-1721205686-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-cooking-3-1721205686-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-357269%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EReva%20finds%20immense%20satisfaction%20knowing%20her%20food%20is%20cooked%20in%20sunlight%20effortlessly.%20%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ECooking%20on%20LPG%20vs%20solar%20stove%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETalking%20about%20the%20pros%20of%20solar%20cooking%2C%20Reva%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9COnce%2C%20I%20add%20vegetables%20and%20other%20ingredients%20in%20the%20solar%20cooker%20then%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20to%20keep%20stirring%20the%20pan%20and%20monitor%20it.%20You%20just%20have%20to%20pull%20out%20the%20tray%20and%20everything%20is%20done.%20This%20system%20is%20more%20convenient%20for%20us%20than%20an%20LPG%20stove%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReva%E2%80%99s%20solar%20cooker%20is%20about%202-feet%20in%20length%20and%20has%20three%20rectangular%20shaped%20containers%20to%20place%20various%20dishes%20like%20%3Cem%3Edaal%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Evegetables%2C%20and%20rice%20separately.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTo%20reduce%20the%20cooking%20time%2C%20I%20use%20%3Cem%3Echana%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20rajma%20soaked%20overnight.%20One%20of%20the%20cons%20of%20this%20system%20is%20that%20we%20cannot%20make%20chapatis%20and%20add%20tadka%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3Edaal%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Instead%2C%20we%20have%20started%20eating%20wheat%20in%20the%20form%20of%20%3Cem%3Edaliya%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20%3Cem%3Ebaati.%20%3C%2Fem%3EAlso%2C%20we%20roast%20and%20add%20cumin%20and%20coriander%20to%20make%20the%20lentil%20taste%20better%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20just%20simplified%20food%20choices%20for%20us%20now.%20The%20taste%20has%20now%20become%20secondary%20for%20us.%20However%2C%20we%20personally%20find%20the%20taste%20to%20be%20slightly%20better%20as%20the%20food%20is%20cooked%20slowly%20and%20the%20taste%20of%20the%20vegetable%20is%20retained%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETalking%20about%20the%20limitation%20of%20the%20set%20up%2C%20Reva%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhile%20we%20do%20most%20of%20the%20cooking%20in%20the%20solar%20cookers%2C%20we%20have%20also%20kept%20firewood%20%3Cem%3Echulha%20%3C%2Fem%3E(stove)%20as%20a%20backup%20for%20cloudy%20and%20rainy%20days.%20We%20collect%20firewood%20from%20trees%20around%20our%20house%20and%20also%20use%20coconut%20shells%20and%20cow%20dung%20cakes%20as%20fuel.%20We%20use%20firewood%20%3Cem%3Echulha%20%3C%2Fem%3Eonly%20once%20or%20twice%20a%20month.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20backup%20for%20cooking%20that%20they%20use%20during%20cloudy%20days%20and%20at%20night%20is%20their%20stored%20solar%20energy.%20Their%20house%20has%20a%20small%20850%20VA%20solar%20inverter%20that%20delivers%20enough%20charge%20for%20low-wattage%20electrical%20appliances.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20fondly%20talks%20about%20how%20she%20repurposed%20and%20converted%20an%20old%20box-type%20solar%20cooker%20into%20a%20food%20dehydrator.%20They%20use%20it%20to%20dehydrate%20and%20preserve%20excess%20fruits%20when%20they%20have%20a%20bounty.%20The%20contraption%20is%20also%20used%20for%20roasting%20grains%2C%20nuts%20and%20even%20drying%20homegrown%20turmeric.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-cooking-4_11zon-1721205784.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Reva%20also%20dehydrates%20excess%20fruits%20in%20sunlight.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-cooking-4_11zon-1721205784.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-cooking-4_11zon-1721205784-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-cooking-4_11zon-1721205784-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2